                <summary>Asher W. Harman writes that his name has been maligned around Staunton for
                    more than two years and most recently in print by Richard Mauzy, editor of the
                    Spectator. Harman insists that he has served his country cheerfully and would
                    never plunder private property or appropriate it for his private use.</summary>
                <note/>
