                </names>
                <summary>The returns from all counties and from the army are not in yet, but
                    Generals Smith and Imboden have received the majority of votes for Governor and
                    Lieutenant Governor. Baldwin, Holliday, Funste, Russell, Johnston, Goode,
                    Wickham, Riv, Collier, Whitfield, and Montague were elected to Congress, with
                    the other races still undecided. Harris, Walker and Kinney were elected to the
                    House of Delegates from Rockingham. Sheffey, Walker, and McCue were elected to
                    the House of Delegates from Augusta. Walker received 1138 votes, Sheffey 113,
                    McCue 1007, Coyner 824, Harman 67, Peyton 386.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
