                <summary>A meeting was held on June 1 at the Augusta County court house to discuss
                    relief measures for the exiles from northwestern Virginia. The Honorable A. H.
                    H. Stuart was chair, with William A. Burke and T. S. Hogshead, Esquires,
                    appointed secretaries. The chair appointed Hugh W. Sheffey, Esq., and the
                    Reverends Campbell, Baker, Latane, Dice, and Taylor to the committee. The
                    committee made several recommendations and collected $865 among the attendees.</summary>
                <note/>
